headline: KeyCorp (KEY) Profit Margin Drops Sharply, Undermining Recent Bullish Narratives
summary: KeyCorp (KEY) posted net profit margins of just 0.7% this quarter compared to 12.5% last year, with EPS dropping as earnings have declined 35.3% per year over the past five years. Despite ongoing pressure on profits and shrinking margins, forecasts now call for annual EPS growth of 13.9% and revenue growth of 6.4% per year. headline: Scotiabank Comments on Expected Contribution from KeyCorp's Third Quarter Earnings
summary: Scotiabank announced today that the expected net income contribution from its ownership interest in KeyCorp will be approximately CAD $74 million in Q4 2025. This contribution represents the Bank's share of KeyCorp's Q3 2025 net income, includes acquisition-related and other accounting impacts, is net of the Bank's associated funding costs and is reported on a one-month lag.

headline: KEY Q3 Deep Dive: Margin Expansion and Strategic Shifts Amid Market Skepticism
summary: Regional banking company KeyCorp (NYSE:KEY) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 176% year on year to $1.89 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.41 per share was 7.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
